00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:10,000
So this is a very interesting and colloquial way of saying immediately.
这是一个非常有趣且口语化的表达方式，意思是“立刻”。

169
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:15,960
So why don't we hear a few examples of how this is used in English.
我们来听几个例子，看看它在英语中怎么用。

170
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:17,920
Example one.
例子一。

171
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:22,000
My boss expects me to come into work at the drop of a hat.
我老板指望我随叫随到去上班。

172
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,800
Example two.
例子二。

173
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:28,520
Laura is always willing to help me at the drop of a hat.
劳拉总是愿意随时帮我。

174
00:08:28,520 --> 00:08:30,280
Example three.
例子三。

175
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:32,200
I can't leave at the drop of a hat.
我不能说走就走。

176
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,600
I need time to prepare.
我需要时间准备。

177
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:38,080
Okay, so as you can see, you can change it for different things but basically you're
好的，如你所见，你可以根据不同的情况调整它，但基本上

178
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:40,360
saying I can't do something immediately.
是在说“我不能立刻做某事”。

179
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:45,400
Yeah, and it is almost always attached to this idea of doing something or going somewhere,
是的，而且它几乎总是和“做某事”或“去某地”、“在某地”这些概念联系在一起。

180
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,400
being somewhere.
对。

181
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:47,400
Very good.
非常好。

182
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,400
At the drop of a hat.
说走就走。

183
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:52,280
Alright, now our final phrase here for this lesson.
好了，现在是我们这节课的最后一个短语。

184
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:57,600
So Veronica was saying I can't go to India at the drop of a hat and she also said I just
维罗妮卡说：我不能说走就走地去印度，她还说：我无法

185
00:08:57,600 --> 00:09:01,280
can't build a relationship on a foundation of lies.
在谎言的基础上建立一段关系。

186
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:03,840
Okay, a foundation of lies.
好的，谎言的基础。

187
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:06,480
To build something on a foundation of lies.
在谎言的基础上建立某物。

188
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,680
Now this is interesting.
这很有意思。

189
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:10,280
Let's take a look at this.
我们来看看这个。

190
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:11,280
Foundation what is that?
基础是什么？

191
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:13,080
Well you know you have a house, right?
你知道房子吧？

192
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:17,400
And the part that's in the ground that supports the house is the foundation.
埋在地里支撑房子的部分就是地基。

193
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:20,440
Okay, so it supports the entire structure.
好的，所以它支撑着整个结构。

194
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:21,440
Right.
对。

195
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:25,680
So here she refers to the lies as the foundation.
所以这里她把谎言比作地基。

196
00:09:25,680 --> 00:09:29,200
And that's no way to start a strong relationship, is it?
这可不是建立牢固关系的方式，对吧？

197
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:30,200
Exactly.
没错。

198
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:35,240
So we use it metaphorically in this way but we can always, but we always have to say it,
所以我们用这个比喻的方式，但我们必须总是说它，

199
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:37,560
but we always have to use the verb build.
但我们必须总是用动词“建立”。

200
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:42,640
Okay, so it's basically to make something on a base of something else, right?
好的，所以基本上就是在某物的基础上建立另一物，对吧？

201
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:48,760
So for example, a strong relationship is built on a foundation of trust.
比如，一段牢固的关系是建立在信任的基础上的。

202
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:53,480
Or this country was built on a foundation of liberty.
或者说，这个国家是建立在自由的基础上的。

203
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:54,480
Very good.
很好。

204
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:57,360
So always use foundation with built.
所以，总是把 foundation 和 built 搭配使用。

205
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:58,360
Very good.
很好。

206
00:09:58,360 --> 00:09:59,360
Very interesting.
非常有趣。

207
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:02,580
And well I think we should listen to this dialogue for the last time and then we'll
嗯，我觉得我们应该再听一遍这段对话，然后

208
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:06,120
come back and talk a little bit more about Veronica and Steven.
回来再聊聊维罗妮卡和史蒂文的事。

209
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:08,720
Veronica, wait.
维罗妮卡，等等。

210
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:12,400
Come on, honey.
来吧，亲爱的。

211
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:15,720
Get back in the car.
回到车里去。

212
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:17,320
Let's talk it over, okay?
我们好好谈谈，好吗？

213
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:18,320
No.
不。

214
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:19,960
I'm tired of your lies.
我受够了你的谎言。

215
00:10:19,960 --> 00:10:21,960
I don't know who you are anymore.
我已经不认识你了。

216
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:26,480
Veronica, it's me, the man that has and always will love you.
维罗妮卡，是我，那个一直爱着你、永远爱你的男人。

217
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:28,880
I'm sorry that I've lied to you, believe me.
对不起，我对你撒了谎，请相信我。

218
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:32,600
It's been hard for me as well and time and again I've thought of coming clean.
对我来说也很难，我一次又一次地想坦白。

219
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:35,300
But I couldn't put you or my mission at risk.
但我不能让你和我的任务陷入危险。

220
00:10:35,300 --> 00:10:36,300
It's all over now.
现在一切都结束了。

221
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:39,400
My assignment is complete and now I have to go back to India.
我的任务完成了，现在我必须回印度了。

222
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:40,400
What?
什么？

223
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:41,700
Are you kidding?
你在开玩笑吗？

224
00:10:41,700 --> 00:10:45,320
Is there anything else I should know before I never see you again?
在我再也见不到你之前，还有什么我应该知道的吗？

225
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:47,680
How could you deceive me like that?
你怎么能这样欺骗我？

226
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:48,680
Yes.
是的。

227
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:56,040
Veronica, I know that this isn't the best time and you probably hate me right now but
维罗妮卡，我知道现在不是时候，你现在可能恨我，但

228
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:58,520
I want to be completely forthright with you.
我想对你完全坦诚。

229
00:10:58,520 --> 00:11:02,760
I know deep in my heart that you are the best thing that has ever happened to me.
我内心深处知道，你是我生命中最美好的事情。

230
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:06,320
Veronica, will you marry me?
维罗妮卡，你愿意嫁给我吗？

231
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:07,960
Come with me to India, baby.
跟我去印度吧，宝贝。

232
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:12,440
I can't make it for everything that's happened but I can promise you my undying love.
我无法弥补过去的一切，但我可以向你保证我永恒的爱。

233
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:16,680
I will be the most devoted husband and I will cherish you always.
我会成为最忠诚的丈夫，永远珍惜你。

234
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:22,200
Stephen, I can't just leave everything at the drop of a hat.
史蒂文，我不能说走就走。

235
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:26,160
With everything that has happened between us, I just don't know you anymore.
我们之间发生了这么多事，我已经不认识你了。

236
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:30,520
I just can't build a relationship on a foundation of lies.
我无法在谎言的基础上建立一段关系。

237
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:34,040
I do love you but I can't go with you.
我确实爱你，但我不能跟你走。

238
00:11:34,040 --> 00:11:35,040
I'm sorry.
对不起。

239
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:36,040
I love you.
我爱你。

240
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:51,200
This is the last call for flight A15 from Los Angeles to Hyderabad.
这是从洛杉矶飞往海得拉巴的A15航班最后一次登机广播。

241
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,440
I'm sorry, sir.
对不起，先生。

242
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:53,800
We can't wait any longer.
我们不能再等了。

243
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:56,000
You must board the plane.
您必须登机了。

244
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:58,080
Are you waiting for someone?
您在等人吗？

245
00:11:58,080 --> 00:12:14,080
I was but I don't think she's coming.
我在等，但我觉得她不会来了。

246
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:18,040
So Marco, I think I see a bit of a tear there in the corner of your eye.
所以马可，我觉得我看到你眼角有点泪光。

247
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:19,040
I'm very sad.
我很难过。

248
00:12:19,040 --> 00:12:21,960
I can't believe he proposed and she just said no.
我不敢相信他求婚了，她却拒绝了。

249
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:22,960
Just like that.
就这样拒绝了。

250
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:24,280
Well, it's not supposed to happen.
嗯，这不应该发生啊。

251
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:30,320
Plus, he was inviting her to India and exotic getaway and promising.
而且，他还邀请她去印度，一个异国风情的度假地，还承诺

252
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:33,240
Exotic getaway for the rest of her life.
给她一辈子的异国风情生活。

253
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:35,760
Well, what do you think will happen?
嗯，你觉得会发生什么？

254
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:37,520
Part 10, it all ends.
第10部分，一切都结束了。

255
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:41,680
So do you think they all just keep on living their separate lives?
所以你觉得他们都会继续各自的生活吗？

256
00:12:41,680 --> 00:12:43,480
Will they meet again?
他们会再见面吗？

257
00:12:43,480 --> 00:12:44,480
Who knows?
谁知道呢？

258
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:47,000
Come to our website and tell us what you think will happen.
来我们的网站告诉我们你认为会发生什么。

259
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,120
So you can find us at EnglishPod.com.
你可以在EnglishPod.com找到我们。

260
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:50,640
All right.
好了。

261
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:55,160
Don't miss our finale of this lesson and until next time, we'll see you guys there.
不要错过我们这节课的大结局，下次再见，我们会在那里等你们。
